Purpose: Why am I doing this?
This assignment teaches you how to automate user account management on a Linux system using Python. 
By completing this task, you’ll gain practical skills for real-world IT system administration, 
including how to create, delete, and modify user accounts using Python scripts and command-line arguments—without any GUI or menu systems.

Skills and Knowledge You Will Gain
-	Automate system administration tasks with Python
-	Learn how to process command-line arguments using argparse
-	Gain hands-on experience with Linux user management
-	Improve your ability to handle errors and validate input
-	Practice writing clean, well-commented, and maintainable Python code
